Product name: SALE Pretty in Pink Sterling Co. Boudoir Doll
Description:
This doll is 28" tall and is one of the rare Sterling Co dolls from the 20's or early 30's. This one is very unusual because Sterling dolls have arm sockets and movable composition arms, but this one has hollow celluloid hands and cotton arms which go through the arm holes.The celluloid hands are very rare, I have only seen a couple of others. This looks to be this way originally from the factory, as she is wearing her original dress and it is nailed on to her. She has a wonderful costume with no holes and only a couple of slight water spots. Her composition is pretty good with splitting at the sides of her neck. She has some crazing on her chest and a very slight amount on her face. She has a couple of cracks at the corner of her eyes and slight restoration eyes and eyeshadow. She is also missing some of her eyelashes, but overall, she shows very well and none of these things detract, She has curley mohair and composition feet with black high heeled shoes, with her original pantaloons.
Was 235, Now 200.
International buyers please contact me for shipping price and listing.

Product name: Bahr & Proschild doll, bru doll, antique doll, vintage doll, german doll, french doll, jumeau doll, Antique Reproduction, bisque doll
Description:
This is a truly beautiful doll that I have enjoyed having on display in my home.
She is an antique reproduction of a Bahr & Proschild doll mold 224 (dimples).  This doll is superbly done.  Bahr & Proschild  was a porcelain factory in Ohrdruf Thuringia Germany and made heads for Bruno Schmidt, Heinrich Stiers, Kley & Hahn and others from 1871 on.  These beautiful dolls were made in the similar style to the ever popular french dolls, and were very highly desired, esp. the closed mouth dolls.
Bahr & Proschild dolls produced before 1910 were marked with just their mold numbers.  This particular reproduction doll is created as such with a simple stamp of 224 on the back of her neck under her hair.  Also on her neck is her artist's name and date, stamped 1985.
This gorgeous doll is 16" tall (minus hat/hair), features beautiful bright clear blue eyes, a wonderful full curly wig, a flawless bisque head and all bisque body, beautiful painting from face down to toes.
Her clothes, pantaloons, slip dress, hat, and lace dress are all handmade and are in beautiful condition.  She is wearing stockings but lacks some shoes.
Damage:  No significant damage or marking is on this doll.  Her arms are a bit loose.  The cording attaching her arms is in fine conditions, but seems to be strung just a bit too big for her.

Product name: Vintage Toy Klik It Poosh-M-Up Toy Pin Game, Marble Game, Vintage Game, Vintage Toy, WITH ORIGINAL BOX
Description:
DETAILS:
You have found a very cool vintage pin/marble game!  I invite you to take a good closer look at the photos to see the condition...it's incredible how great of shape it is in for its age. The white marbles you see in the photo are also included.  The playing surface from a heavy fiberboard material.  This is surrounded by a steel band.  There are Indians, numbers, and other figures displayed on the board.  There is a spring arm on the right side which shoots the marble into the main playing area...similar to a pinball machine.  However, this isn't a pinball game.  There are no levers on the side like a pinball game.  There is another metal piece at the bottom, in the middle of the game.  If the marble ends up in this area, the metal lever can shoot the marble straight back through the middle of the game.
The directions on the game read:
"Each player shoots all the marbles, one at a time. When a marble rolls into one of the "Klickers" it is replayed from that point until it gets into a scoring pocket."
CONDITION:
There is some mild rust, which you can see in one of the photos.  It looks like this is the only part with rust (this is the end that has been sticking out of the box all these years.)
This game does come with the original box.  However, the box has seen better days, but perhaps since the game has been in it all these years, that is probably why the game is in great shape. 
APPROX MEASUREMENTS:
Without the box, the game itself measures 24" long and 13" wide.

Description:
1950s revival of the cart wheel hat - or cartwheel hat. This one is amazing in navy blue straw with two tone blue velvet twisted trim and a rhinestone garnish. This hat is by new york/Paris designer, Henry Ross. A cartwheel hat (also cart wheel hat) is a wide brimmed circular or saucer-shaped design.  Typically, it is worn at an angle to show off the curve of the brim, rather than being worn at the back of the head in the manner of a halo hat. This one comes with a hat pin to help you keep it in place. 
Because these work into the hair style, they are designed to fit all head sizes. This measures 15 1/4 inches from front to back of brim. The back brim is narrower than the front. Condition is very, very good, with the slightest bit of soil to the ribbon (no more than what you can see in photo) and a pin hole in the ribbon from hat pin use. 
Enjoy... this is an amazing hat.

Product name: Carnival Cruise Light Card¬Æ card key switch activator
Description:
Several Carnival cruise ships use card key switches to conserve energy in guest cabins.
The Carnival suggestion is to use one of your room keys - which often results in a forgotten key when leaving the room.
So I have created the Light Card¬Æ card key switch activator!
It consists of a PVC card with artwork printed directly on the card (making it waterproof & long-lasting!) and a magnet on the back. 
Put it in the slot while you're in the room, and then pull it out and use the attached magnet to hang it on the wall above the slot while you're out. 
No more forgotten room keys!
~~Important! Be sure to remove completely when you leave, as stateroom hosts are in the habit of grabbing the card in the slot on the way out and in their haste may inadvertently take yours!
~~Also, be sure to hang on the wall above the card slot and not on the door - the motion of the door can cause the cards to slide and possibly fall off.
Can be used over and over for all your cruises using card key switch technology, and hung on your fridge as a memento in between!
Please note - "How Many?" will be multiplied by "Quantity" selected to give final amount of cards ordered. For example, if you select 2 under "Quantity" and then "Set of 4 cards" under "How Many?" you will be ordering 8 cards (2 x 4).

Our Strict Disclaimer And Design Limitations Regarding Industry Standard Woven Labels. 
Please Note that woven labels are not like printed labels so it is not possible to do lots of stuff like giving shadow effect . Another issue is color matching, it is not possible to match the Pantone or other color matching,
we always try to match the best possible shade (if we don't find one then we will contact you before taking any step) This is industry standard for woven labels.
With weaving, it is impossible to have 100% detail to match your graphic art, as these are literally stitched/woven labels and NOT printed labels.  
The size after cut and folded finished both have -2mm tolerances. The colors of yarn can have tolerances of up to 15%.   please note that vertical line, horizontal line  circles, curves and slants are very tough with weaving, it will have a step to the next stitch line in the weaving process.
Also, some letters may be larger, etc.   
If you need 100% matching of fine detail, no color of yarn "peeking" through a white background from yarn, you need printed labels instead of premium woven. The yarn/threads of woven labels may have different thicknesses hence limitations to some fine detail.
By ordering woven labels you understand and agree with these industry standard tolerances and are approved by you the customer upon placing this order. The method of weaving labels involves moving parts and moving loom machinery and therefore the possibility of the above variances These are NOT printed labels!  While we try our best to avoid any tolerance, these tolerances above are industry standard for all woven labels.

Know Your "True" Size
If you're not really sure about your "true" shoe size, it's a good idea to find out before you order. Product name: Short Moccasins With Fringe, Traditional Native American Plains Style, Made to Order, Handmade, Handsewn, Powwow, Earthing Shoes, Natural
Description:
Handmade to order, handsewn Native American Short Moccasins with Handcut Fringe, Plains Style with Leather Lace Tie
Traditional short moccasins, handmade by Lakota artist, Crowwolf. Each pair is custom made to order. Soles are made of sturdy buffalo hide, hold up great for daily wear and are ultra comfortable on the feet. Uppers are made of quality, natural color elk hide and handsewn with sinew. Fringe is handcut.
Moccasins are unisex and custom made to order (Size options are listed above, childrens sizes also available upon request). If possible, please send measurement of foot legnth and width as well. This helps Crowwolf custom fit moccasin as close as possible.
Moccasins are made traditionally to be worn without socks and fit the foot snug. Moccasins will stretch some once worn and will mold to your foot shape. If you would like to wear your moccasins with socks, please let us know so we may allow for the extra room.
Beading designs are available at an extra charge.
Various leather options also available. Pair pictured is made from buttery soft, natural/tan color elk hide.
*Please note, all of our items are handmade and one of a kind. The pictures of our moccasins and other custom made to order pieces are to show the workmanship and quality. Leather texture and finish varies from hide to hide. Leather color varies some from hide to hide, one gold elk hide may be a bit lighter or darker than another, for example. We use quality hides from animals humanely treated and DO NOT support factory farming of any animal. Each order is handmade, moccasins are handsewn one stitch at a time and no machine is involved in the creation process. Crowwolf honors the ancient traditions of the Lakota in his handcrafted leather designs.
Each design handcrafted by Crowwolf and/or Katy is cleansed within the sacred smoke with prayer.
All items in our shop are shipped USPS Priority mail, insured and tracked within the domestic US. All orders outside the domestic US are shipped USPS First Class mail, insured and tracked.
Please allow 3-5 weeks for shipping as each pair is custom made.
